🌈 🐈‍⬛ Who remembers making Rainbow scratch paper using crayons and a straightened out paper clip!??? Now they sell it at Michael's and its so awesome! Anyway, I had a vision flashback to this 80's childhood happy fun craft time I use to do and decided to make it out of glass. Rainbow Scratch Kitty is actually free hand carved using a foredom tool then heated back up and flame polished. And its up for grabs (link in my bio).

Data update, FINALLY....
So, we knew that tumor was not a benign fatty lypoma, so this bad news could of been way worse. Diagnosis: Spindle Cell Tumor, a locally invasive liposarcoma. The best news is that it's a low grade tumor. While the Dr. told me that means it won't spread beyond the area it sprouted up in... my over obsessive googling says that low grade tumor has less than a 25% chance of spreading beyond its original growth area. But, even when removed, it is likely to grow back in the same spot because these type of "locally invasive" tumors shoot out little tentacles and if you don't remove every single cell, it will likely grow back. 

Dr. Todd said that this news means that whatever is going on in her chest xray has nothing to do with this tumor (and thats also good news). So. At this point, he advises that we re-xray her chest one more time (5-6 weeks after the first xray was done) to see if that mystery "spot" has grown at all. If it hasnt grown, amazing. It's nothing scary and we can move forward with the TPLO surgery to repair her leg. Then when her 8 week leg xray gets done, we will xray the chest again just to be safe.

We are still trying to wrap our heads around all of this. Doing lots of research and planning to meet up with the oncologist to go over everything in more detail with her. If any of you out there have any experience or advice to give around this type of cancer in dogs, please DM me. If any of you are radiologists and would like to review her chest xrays and give your input, please DM me. 

Thank you all for the love and concern for Data. She is our family and we want to make sure we do everything we can to make her quality of life exceptional. As of today, she is feeling great and enjoying rolling around in the Saturday sun. She's also super bored and has officially started annoying Kevin and I because she's so tired of being stuck at home with a bum leg!

Has this ever happened to your cat? It only took one occurrence with China for me to start religiously cutting the handles on brown bags left out for the cats to play in. But thanks to human error and an ornery door knob that requires a firm closure to properly shut the door, Beatrix went on an adventure in the one room the cats are never allowed: the bedroom with our entire glass collection in it. Somehow all of the glass remained untouched (🙌) but clearly a massive ruckus occurred. I found the rest of the bag under the kitchen table. I came home and was downstairs with Data when Bea showed up asking for rescue. She was very shaken up and did not enjoy getting around on 3 legs, like Romano. Long story short: if you leave paper bags out for your cats, please cut the handles so they don't become a frantic scared rocket of fear and anxiety. Thanks for coming to my Ted Talk.
